30|$|In the {{following}} section, we will first introduce the research design and method {{used for this}} study (Sect.  2). Section  3 focuses on how weather forecasts and warnings are disseminated to emergency managers by the German national weather service (Deutscher Wetterdienst, DWD) and what actions are taken by the emergency services to anticipate and respond to severe weather, with an emphasis on situation assessments. We discuss the measures taken and the relevance of various information sources like official weather <b>warnings</b> in <b>decision</b> making (Sect.  4), and draw conclusions (Sect.  5).|$|R
